text.section:
"Load-bearing portions of the home" means the load-bearing portions of the:
Foundation system and footings;
Beams;
Girders;
Lintels;
Columns;
Walls and partitions;
Floor systems; and
Roof framing system.

section.section:
"New home" does not include:
Outbuildings, including detached garages and detached carports, except outbuildings that contain plumbing, electrical, heating, cooling, or ventilation systems serving the new home;
Driveways;
Walkways;
Patios and decks;
Boundary walls;
Retaining walls not necessary for the structural stability of the new home;
Landscaping;
Fences;
Off-site improvements;
Appurtenant recreational facilities; and
Other similar items as determined by the Secretary of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation.

text.section:
"Plumbing systems" means:
Gas supply lines and fittings;
Water supply, waste, and vent pipes and their fittings;
Septic tanks and their drain fields; and
Water, gas, and sewer service piping and their extensions to the tie-in of a public utility connection; or
On-site wells and sewage disposal systems.
